name: Chon-Ji
meaning: Chon Ji means literally the Heaven and The Earth. It is in the orient interpreted as the creation of the world or the beginning of human history. Therefore it is the initial pattern performed by the beginner. This pattern consists of two separate parts, one to represent the Heaven, the other the Earth.

name: Dan-Gun
meaning: Dan Gun is named after the holy Dan Gun, the legindary founder of Korea in the year 2333 B.C.

name: Do-San
meaning: Do San is the pseudonym of the patriot Ahn Chang-Ho (1876-1938). The 24 movements represent his entire life which he devoted to furthering the education of Korea and its independence movement.

name: Choong-Jang
meaning: Choong-Jang is the pseudonym of General Kim Duk Ryang who lived during the Lee Dynasty, 14th century.

name: Won-Hyo
meaning: Won-Hyo is named after the monk who introduced Buddhism to the Silla Dynasty. This is a dummy entry used as an example pattern.
